- Variable: named container for particular type of data used to hold a value.
            has unique name, returns value whenever called
            variable memorizes value for us
            must be declared first
            DataType variableName;
            (int  quantity;)
            Declaration (creation of variable): int quantity;
                         double area;
                         double pi;
            Assignment (store value to variable): quantity = 3;
                        area = 116.6
                        pi = 3.14159...
            Initialization: when value assigned to variable for the first time




- Data Types: defines values a variable can hold
               - Primitive Data Types: byte, short,int, long -> used for int values/whole nums
                                       float, double -> floating nums such as 1.5 etc
                                       char -> used for single character at a time
                                       boolean -> true false expressions
               - Non-Primitive Types: String, Array, Classes, Interface

- Boolean data type: represents concepts of true or false :
    -> boolean isMarreid = false;
    -> boolean isDoorOpen = true; -> isDoorOpen = false
-Char sata type: can only store single character at a time
     -> ways to get single character: e.g. you want to print A
     char ch1 = 'A'; (used most of the time)
     char ch2 = 65; (decimal value of character)
     char ch3 = 0x41; (hexadecimal value of character)
     char ch4 = '\u0041'; (UTF-16(Unicode))


- String: sequence of characters, using("") -> e.g. String greeting;
                                                    greeting = "hello World!";
                                                    String name = "Wooden Spoon";
   -> concatenation: - action of linking two strings together to get enw string using the "+" operator
                     - to make concatenation work we need to make sure there is a string on either left or right side
                       e.g. String st1 = "...";
                       String st2 = "...";
                       String afterConcat = str1 + str2;
                       sout(afterConcat);
                       OR concat int
                       int num = 5;
                       sout ("The value is" +num);
- constants: unchangable , value can only be assigned only one time and not be changed anymore
